11. The semiconductor device of claim 1 wherein a twin word line driver coupled to FET comprising: 
a word line write (WLW) port; 
a first diode coupled to the WLW port to provide a pulsed first level offset; 
a word line read (WLR) port; and 
a second diode coupled to the WLR port to provide a pulsed second level offset.

